[[Image:British forces in Egypt.jpg|thumb|Stamp used by the British Forces in Egypt.]] '''A military stamp''', is a [[postage stamp]] used by a military organisation, in time of war, or while ensuring a peace keeping operation. Often the letters will be transported by the army itself until they reach the country of destination. These stamps were widely used during [[World War II]] by soldiers wishing to send mail home to their families. The usage of these stamps has been somewhat phased out by the appearance of electronic means of communication. Some army issues include: *China Expeditionary Forces (1900-1921) *[[Indian Army during World War I#Expeditionary Force|Indian Expeditionary Forces]] (1914-1922) *[[Postage stamps and postal history of German East Africa#Mafia Island|British occupation of Mafia Island]] (1915-1916) *British Field Office in Salonica (1916) *Nyasaland Field Force (1916) *[[Egyptian Expeditionary Force]] (1918) *[[Indian Expeditionary Force D]] (1919) *British Forces in Egypt (1932-1939) *[[British military post offices in Africa#Middle East Forces|Middle East Forces]] (1942-1947) *[[British military post offices in Africa#East Africa Forces|East Africa Forces]] (1943-1946) *Indian National Army (World War II) *[[Indian Army United Nations peacekeeping missions#Past Missions|Indian Custodian Forces in Korea]] (1953) *[[International Control Commission|International Commission in Indo-China]] (1954-1968) *[[Indian Army United Nations peacekeeping missions#Past Missions|Indian UN Force in Congo]] (1962) *Indian UN Force in Gaza (1965) <gallery> File:India CEF 1913-21 ScM24.jpg|A stamp of the China Expeditionary Forces. File:India IEF 1914 ScM34.jpg|A stamp of the Indian Expeditionary Forces. File:GermanEastAfrica2-5heller1915hohenzollern-grmafiaovpt.jpg|A stamp for the British occupation of Mafia Island. File:Stamp Palestine 1918 20pi.jpg|A stamp of the Egyptian Expeditionary Force. File:Stamp Mesopotamia 1919 0.5a Mosul.jpg|A stamp for the India